{meta: title I Want You Free}
{meta: artist Jean Shepard}
{meta: writer Martha Sharp}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]If my words should ever strike [F]you
[G7]Like the rattlin' of [C]chains
[F]And my voice should ever make you
[D7]Long for trains and boats and [G7]planes
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[C]May I live a million [F]years
[G7]And never feel your touch [C]again
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
I want you free
[G7]I want you only if and when you want [C]me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[F]If you ever get to feelin'
[G7]That you've stayed away too [C]long
[F]And somethin' I have said
[D7]Makes you dread just comin' [G7]home
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[C]May I live a lonely [F]life
[G7]Without a love to call my [C]own
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
I want you free
[G7]I want you only if and when you want [C]me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
[F]I want you free I want you [C]free
[F]Unwilling love ain't good enough for [G7]me
[C]Though heaven [F]knows I love your lovin' [C]me
[G7]I want you free I want you [C]free
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 8}
[F]If you ever cease to love me
[G7]Never think that I won't [C]know
[F]If you ever come to me just cause
[D7]There's no place else to [G7]go
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 9}
[C]May the next one that you [F]love
[G7]Destroy your spirit and your [C]soul
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 10}
I want you free
[G7]I want you only if and when you want [C]me
{end_of_verse}
